column5: Well i finally found the crappie in my home lake, figures they weren't at the same spot as last year around this time but they are very black  Biggest         I think i would of caught more if i had live bait.
that is a huge black slab! good job!
Now there's a nice slab!!!  Live bait may catch more but it's not as fun if you ask me when compared to fishing a jig or fly.
And less deep/foul hooking.  Nice Crappie though!
Noice!!!! Send us more pics like that
Good on you for catching him on an artifical.  Are you using gulp?  Thats a giant slab fer sure.  Must have been a great dual.  Congrats.

Nope just a small Chartreuse Grub 2" and a Red jig head to match the body of the grub and a small split shot about 6" from the jig. i was very surprise to get them on the Grub usually there on minnows til mid June.  The majority of Slabs i catch are about 10-16".  hehe opps more pictures to come as i hit them harder
